{"lemma": "جَرِيبٌ", "slug": "جَرِيبٌ", "root": "ج.ر.ب", "root_slug": "ج-ر-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ج-ر-ب", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n5440"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "dry measure for grain", "fa": "واحد اندازه‌گیری غلات", "ur": "غلات کی پیمائش", "tr": "tahıl ölçüsü", "id": "satuan ukuran gandum", "bn": "শস্যের পরিমাপক", "es": "medida seca de grano", "fr": "mesure sèche de grain", "de": "Trockenmaß für Getreide", "ru": "мера для зерна", "zh": "谷物干量单位"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a dry measure for grain, peck"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a division of cropland, a certain square measure varying between country and period, jerib, as much as can be sown from the grain measure"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "follicle"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Borrowed from Aramaic גְּרִיוָא (gəriwā), גְּרִיבָא (gəriḇā), ܓܪܝܻܒܳܐ (gəriḇā, “a dry measure; a measure of land”), from Imperial Aramaic 𐡂𐡓𐡉𐡅 (gryw), of Old Iranian origin, Middle Persian [script needed] (glyw' /⁠griw⁠/), Parthian [script needed] (gryw' /⁠griw⁠/), also found in Old Armenian գրիւ (griw), probably unrelated to the homonymous Iranian words for “neck; throat” but likely related to Proto-Indo-Iranian *grabʰ (“to grab, to seize”), from Proto-Indo-European *gʰrebʰ- (compare the Sanskrit root ग्रभ् (grabh)), if this is not the same word as treated under جِرَاب (jirāb) denoting a kind of bag, see there.\n\nDiminutive of جِرَاب (jirāb, “follis”)."}, "ipa": ["/d͡ʒa.riːb/", "/d͡ʒu.rajb/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n5440", "headword_ar": "جَرِيبٌ", "root": "jrb", "body": [{"kind